text:
The staff seemed disengaged and uninterested in providing service; I stood there for quite a while, hoping someone would approach me or even acknowledge my presence.

While I understand that sometimes businesses have an off day, the lethargy in service was palpable. It made what should have been an enjoyable experience  feel more like an inconvenience. I hope the management takes note of this and encourages their team to engage more actively with customers.
I enjoy their gado gado salad and Ayam Bakar rice.   Food served super fast.  Decent Indonesian cuisine around the neighbourhood.

The food served was fast, the food was good and delicious. The downside is, there's not a lot of food to order of.. And the price was not that cheap yet not expensive. So so for me. You can self service to take the tap water.

Unassuming, affordable, quality indo food in the heartland. In case you need a Gado Gado and Sop Buntut fix, this is the place to visit.

Located right smack outside Buangkok Mrt Station. Sop Buntut at $7 is legit and Gado Gado at $5.90 is generous with portion.
Ordered grilled chicken. Rice and chicken super dry. And no sauce. Worse grilled chicken I ever had
